    "# Introduction to Arithmetic Expressions\n",
    "\n",
    "Arithmetic expressions are mathematical statements that combine numbers and operators to perform calculations. In programming and data science, understanding how to use arithmetic expressions is essential for data manipulation and analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Common Arithmetic Operators\n",
    "\n",
    "Here are some common arithmetic operators used in programming:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Addition (`+`)**: Adds two numbers.\n",
    "- **Subtraction (`-`)**: Subtracts one number from another.\n",
    "- **Multiplication (`*`)**: Multiplies two numbers.\n",
    "- **Division (`/`)**: Divides one number by another.\n",
    "- **Modulus (`%`)**: Returns the remainder of a division operation.\n",
    "- **Exponentiation (`**`)**: Raises a number to the power of another number.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Examples of Arithmetic Expressions\n",
    "\n",
    "Here are some examples of arithmetic expressions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Addition**: \n",
    "   - `5 + 3` results in `8`\n",
    "   \n",
    "2. **Subtraction**: \n",
    "   - `10 - 4` results in `6`\n",
    "   \n",
    "3. **Multiplication**: \n",
    "   - `7 * 6` results in `42`\n",
    "   \n",
    "4. **Division**: \n",
    "   - `20 / 4` results in `5.0`\n",
    "   \n",
    "5. **Modulus**: \n",
    "   - `10 % 3` results in `1` (remainder of 10 divided by 3)\n",
    "   \n",
    "6. **Exponentiation**: \n",
    "   - `2 ** 3` results in `8` (2 raised to the power of 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "Understanding these basic arithmetic expressions is fundamental for performing calculations in data science and programming.\n"
   ]
  },
